title: For Trade:  Western Derringer 22lr
postcontent:
I have for trade a derringer made in 1968. It was imported and sold through herter's when they were in business from the 1930 up till 1981 when they filed bankruptcy. This one is in 22lr caliber. Has steel hammer, trigger, pins, screws and barrel inset into the casting. Not thin liners like a lot of the new derringers have but actual steel barrels inset into barrel casting. 

Has the eagle over N proof marks for nitro proofed. For smokeless powder. Also has the ULM proof house mark which is the stag antler and date of 68 next to it. Meaning it was proofed in 1968 when it was made. 

For anyone not familiar with the ulm proof house they are the ones who HK exclussively goes through and walther uses them as well as far back as WWII. They are a quality proofhouse and proof quality firearms in return. 

Marked Western Derringer, Made in Germany. Not made by rohm either. It has the Kaschie factory stamp under the grip and Kaschie manufactured lighters from 1923 to early 60s. They made lots of metal goods for the german military during WWII. Just as their lighters are quality and collectible so are their derringers. 

This derringer has nice grips, black plastic checkered, nickel plated finish, nice steel barrels with shine and crisp rifling. Locks up tight, fires great. Has a safety as well. Basically a copy of the Old West  Remington model 95 derringers in 41RF.

Not looking to sell it. Looking to trade for a mosin nagant rifle either long rifle or carbine version. no sporterized stocks though. Just a shootable bore not pitted up is fine with me. 

Can call or text me REDACTED anytime. Can meet within a decent distance.
